Ralph Smith wrote:
&gt; I don&#39;t know why people can&#39;t hear

my voices I get with 



&gt; the boxes. I guess maybe I&#39;m the they only are meant for me to

hear I



&gt;  don&#39;t know. They are clear to me. It&#39;s a mystery to me.

Or maybe there is also a learning curve on the other side with figuring out
how to use the box effectively.

&gt; Maybe I&#39;ll 



&gt; get some that you all can hear one of these days. I clean them up 



&gt; like I do with tradional EVPs maybe I should do them differently. 

One thing I want to experiment with is to feed them through a voice
recognition program.  Years (OK, decades) ago when I got my degree in
linguistics, I took some graduate coursework in how the brain perceives
spoken language.  There is a degree to which a sound can waiver from the
actual target but still have the brain recognize it.  The recordings we get
remind me a lot of experiments I did in college where we would program a
computer to pronounce a word with a sound somewhere between, for example,
&quot;b&quot; and &quot;p&quot;, combine it with some more sounds to make a short word, like
&quot;bat&quot; or &quot;pat&quot;, and see which way the subject perceived it.  If the spirits
have trouble getting the message through clearly on their end, looking at
ways to interpret it better on our end might help.

I 



&gt; seem to get alot of voices talking to each other and hearing many 



&gt; names being said do you people hear that also ? I get a ton of 



&gt; Tradional EVPs it seems everywhere I go. My group S.P.I.R.I.T. 



&gt; Paranormal Investigation Team of central PA will be doing an 



&gt; investigation at the Jenny Wade House in Gettysburg,PA. March 7th

I 



&gt; can&#39;t wait for that one. 

I&#39;m green with envy. =)

&gt; I hope to take some boxes there

and see what



&gt;  I get. 

I&#39;ll be looking forward to hearing them.  One tip - if you are using a
hand-held recorder, be careful to keep it far enough away from your box that
it doesn&#39;t cause interference itself.  I noticed a big difference in how
staticy my recordings out in the field were over the weekend vs. the ones
I&#39;ve been recording directly into my computer.  I guess I ought to invest in
an external mic for the hand-held.


Nellie




